-- Toulouse, Munster, Northampton, Bath Lead Groups in Heineken Cup Rugby
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2010-10-16T19:22:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-16/toulouse-munster-northampton-bath-lead-groups-in-heineken-cup-rugby.html
Defending champion Toulouse,
Munster, Northampton and Bath all won to move to the top of
their groups in European rugby’s Heineken Cup.  Toulouse routed Newport Gwent Dragons 40-19 to take the
lead in Pool 6, Munster easily beat Toulon 45-18 in Pool 3,
Northampton won 31-27 in Edinburgh in Pool 1 and Bath downed
Aironi 22-6 in Pool 4.  Leinster edged Saracens 25-23 to increase its lead in Pool
2 over Clermont Auvergne, which lost 16-9 to Racing Metro.  Biarritz hosts Ulster, Glasgow Warriors visit London Wasps,
Perpignan faces Benetton and Leicester Tigers meet Scarlets in
tomorrow’s games. Yesterday, Ospreys beat London Irish 27-16 and
Castres defeated Cardiff 27-20.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  